The experts wonder, among other things, at what time the saurians divided into three major evolution groups: the theropods (carnivores) that include the tyrannosaurus and the veciraptor that appeared later and which descend the birds, the sauropods, quadrupeds on the long neck, and those related to them and the Ornithischian herbivores of which are part the species such as the triratops and the stegosaurus.
