These small air pockets make it easier for birds to breathe compared to mammals.
It appears that in Tawa found, vertebrae were also partially filled with air.
According to Randall Irmis, the Tawa is one of the oldest theropods with small air bags in its bones.
As the related lineage of the immense sauropods also had air bags and a light bone, it may be thought that their common ancestor already had this beneficial innovation.
