In this regard, he recalled that the Competitiveness Plan, included in the Integrated Plan for the Automotive Sector (IPA), has allocated EUR 800 million to projects of 19 manufacturers and 137 ancillary companies, which have mobilised an investment of more than EUR 3,000 million.
The Chief Executive explained that this investment was intended for both the development of new models and the modernization of existing products and processes.
Zapatero also focused on government demand support measures, in reference to Plan 2000E, implemented in collaboration with autonomous communities and automotive companies.
According to the President, this plan reduced the average emissions of new vehicles marketed on the Spanish market by 6% and contributed to a "high increase" in registrations, which increased by "40%" in November.
