Internet auctions of crash cars
Last October, the Solera group bought Autoonline, an Internet platform for the sale of damaged cars, motorcycles and special vehicles.
The transaction involved a cost of €59.5 million for 85% of the company's capital, which could extend next year to the remaining 15%.
The objective of the acquisition was to offer more value-added services to its customers, with the possibility of access to an immense international market.
This estimate and sales service is intended exclusively for professionals in the sector, such as insurance companies, experts, rental companies, garages, caskets and professional sellers who must be registered before starting operations.
This platform was established in 1996 in Germany and operates more than 650,000 operations across Europe, including 500,000 in Germany.
Among its main markets are Spain, Greece, Poland and Turkey.
There are currently more than 1500 vendors and 4000 experts registered on the site.
It manages 3,000 ads per day and on the Spanish market, 100 new ads are published every day.
