Four-step garage quote
With the Auda-Taller tool, the Audadex company ensures that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, look for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
Ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passenger cars, 109 all-terrain vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are necessary.
Once the model to be repaired is identified with its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and the required part is selected.
The user can include variables such as labour price, increases or discounts, then he can print the quote to give it to the customer.
AudaWorker is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a reference catalogue.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one for garages does not include estimated labour time.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be credited.
Currently, Audadx is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with a very good eye, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inner face.
